Package: hierfstat
Version: 0.04-20
Date: 2015-11-24
Title: Estimation and Tests of Hierarchical F-Statistics
Authors@R: c(person("Jerome","Goudet",role=c("aut","cre"),email="jerome.goudet@unil.ch"),
             person("Thibaut","Jombart",role="aut",email="t.jombart@imperial.ac.uk"))
Author: Jerome Goudet [aut, cre],
        Thibaut Jombart [aut]
Maintainer: Jerome Goudet <jerome.goudet@unil.ch>
Imports: gtools,ade4,adegenet
Suggests: ape,pegas,
    knitr
Description: This R package allows the estimation of hierarchical F-statistics from haploid or diploid genetic data 
    with any numbers  of levels in the hierarchy, following the algorithm of Yang (Evolution, 1998, 52(4):950-956). 
	Functions are also given to test via randomisations the significance of each F and variance components,  
	using the likelihood-ratio statistics G -see Goudet etal. (Genetics, 1996, 144(4): 1933-1940).
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
License: GPL (>=2)
URL: http://www.r-project.org, http://github.com/jgx65/hierfstat
BugReports: https://github.com/jgx65/hierfstat/issues
VignetteBuilder: knitr
